This paper focuses on the detection of unknown web vulnerabilities using unsupervised learning techniques, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also utilizes advanced neural network architectures for anomaly detection, which suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the deployment of web applications in containers, which relates to software engineering (cs.SE). Finally, the use of neural networks for anomaly detection suggests a focus on neural networks (cs.NE).
